<DOC><DOCNO> AP880224-0165 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-24-88 1447EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People-Schuller     02-24 0214</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People-Schuller,0218</SECOND><HEAD>TV Evangelist Robert Schuller Says He Won't Be Caught in SexScandal</HEAD><DATELINE>GARDEN GROVE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Evangelist Robert Schuller says hehas no need to worry about facing a damaging sex scandal likefellow TV preachers Jim Bakker and Jimmy Swaggart because he'snever been unfaithful to his wife.   ``I can tell you right here and now, as far as Robert Schulleris concerned, I have had sex with only one woman _ my wife _ andthe first time was my wedding night,'' the founder of OrangeCounty's Crystal Cathedral church said Tuesday.   Bakker lost his TV ministry last year and was defrocked by theAssemblies of God Church after he admitted to a sexual tryst withformer church secretary Jessica Hahn. The same congregationsuspended Swaggart after he admitted last week to having visited areputed prostitute in a motel.   Schuller, 61, made his remarks to approximately 1,000 peopleattending a special Tuesday night meeting where it was announcedthat the Rev. Herman ``Bud'' Ridder, president of the CrystalCathedral since 1983, was resigning.   Schuller founded the Crystal Cathedral, originally known as theGarden Grove Community Church, in the mid-1950s. The church, knownfor its stunning crystal cathedral headquarters in Garden Grove,now boasts more than 5,500 members.</TEXT></DOC>